comment:
*   IMS supplementary services configs. This groups the configs required for
     *   supplementary services (SS) like XCAP over UT,
     *   Unstructured Supplementary Service Data(USSD).

variables.name: KEY_PREFIX
variables.comment: Prefix of all imsss.KEY_* constants.

variables.name: KEY_UT_REQUIRES_IMS_REGISTRATION_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag that controls whether XCAP over UT status need to be * dependent on IMS registration. * *

If {@code true}: XCAP over UT status need to be * dependent on IMS registration. * {@code false} otherwise.

variables.name: KEY_UT_SUPPORTED_WHEN_ROAMING_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag that controls whether XCAP over UT is supported * when on roaming network. * *

If {@code true}: XCAP over UT is supported when on * roaming network. * {@code false} otherwise.

variables.name: KEY_USE_CSFB_ON_XCAP_OVER_UT_FAILURE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag that controls whether Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) * option is available when XCAP over UT fails. * *

If {@code false}: XCAP over UT only with no CSFB option. * If XCAP over UT fails, return error. * if {@code true}, Use CSFB if XCAP over UT fails.

variables.name: KEY_UT_SUPPORTED_WHEN_PS_DATA_OFF_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag that controls whether XCAP over UT is enabled or not * when PS data is turned off. * *

If {@code true}: XCAP over UT is enabled when PS data is off. * {@code false}: Otherwise. * * Reference: IR.92 Section 5.5.1

variables.name: KEY_NETWORK_INITIATED_USSD_OVER_IMS_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag that controls whether network initiated USSD over IMS is * supported by the UE. * *

If {@code true}: Support Available.{@code false}: Otherwise. * Reference: 3GPP 24.390.

variables.name: KEY_UT_IPTYPE_HOME_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the 'XCAP over UT' IP Type when device is * on Home Network. * *

Possible values are, * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IPV4V6}, * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IP}, * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IPV6} * * If key is invalid or not configured, the default value * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IPV4V6} will apply.

variables.name: KEY_UT_IPTYPE_ROAMING_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the 'XCAP over UT' IP Type when device is roaming. * *

Possible values are, * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IPV4V6}, * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IP}, * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IPV6} * If key is invalid or not configured, the default value * {@link ApnSetting#PROTOCOL_IPV4V6} will apply.

variables.name: KEY_UT_AS_SERVER_FQDN_STRING
variables.comment:
* Specifies the XCAP Application Server fully qualified domain name (FQDN). *

Reference: 24.623 Section 5.2.3.

variables.name: KEY_UT_AS_SERVER_PORT_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the XCAP Application Server Remote port.
         * As XCAP is a usage of HTTP, the default value is same as HTTP, i.e. 80.

variables.name: KEY_UT_TRANSPORT_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the preferred transport to be used for XCAP over UT. * *

Possible values are, * {@link Ims#PREFERRED_TRANSPORT_TCP}, * {@link Ims#PREFERRED_TRANSPORT_TLS} * *

If key is invalid or not configured, the default value * {@link Ims#PREFERRED_TRANSPORT_TCP} will apply.

variables.name: KEY_XCAP_OVER_UT_SUPPORTED_RATS_INT_ARRAY
CALL_WAITING_SYNC_NONE
variables.comment:
* Do not synchronize the user's call waiting setting with the network. Call waiting is
         * always enabled on the carrier network and the user setting for call waiting is applied
         * on the terminal side. If the user disables call waiting, the call will be rejected on
         * the terminal.

variables.name: CALL_WAITING_SYNC_USER_CHANGE
variables.comment:
* The change of userâ€™s setting is always passed to the carrier network
         * and then synchronized to the terminal based call waiting solution over IMS.
         * If changing the service over the carrier network is not successful,
         * the setting over IMS shall not be changed.

variables.name: CALL_WAITING_SYNC_FIRST_POWER_UP
variables.comment:
* Activate call waiting on the carrier network when the device boots or a subscription
         * using this carrier is loaded. Call waiting is always considered enabled on the carrier
         * network and the user setting for call waiting is applied on the terminal side only. If
         * the user disables call waiting, the call will be rejected on the terminal.
         * The mismatch between CS calls and IMS calls can happen when the network based call
         * waiting service is in disabled state in the legacy 3G/2G networks while it's enabled
         * in the terminal side.

variables.name: CALL_WAITING_SYNC_FIRST_CHANGE
variables.comment:
* Activate call waiting on the carrier network when the user enables call waiting the
         * first time. Call waiting is then always considered enabled on the carrier network. If
         * the user disables call waiting, the setting will only be applied to the terminal based
         * call waiting service and the call will be rejected on the terminal.
         * The mismatch between CS calls and IMS calls can happen when the network based call
         * waiting service is in disabled state in the legacy 3G/2G networks while it's enabled
         * in the terminal side. However, if the user retrieves the setting again when the device
         * is in the legacy 3G/2G networks, the correct state will be shown to the user.

variables.name: CALL_WAITING_SYNC_IMS_ONLY
variables.comment:
* Do not synchronize the call waiting service state between the carrier network and
         * the terminal based IMS call waiting service. If the user changes the call waiting setting
         * when IMS is registered, the change will only be applied to the terminal based call
         * waiting service. If IMS is not registered when call waiting is changed, synchronize this
         * setting with the carrier network.

variables.name: CALL_WAITING_SYNC_MAX
variables.comment: @hide

variables.name: KEY_TERMINAL_BASED_CALL_WAITING_SYNC_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating the way to synchronize the setting between CS and IMS. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #CALL_WAITING_SYNC_NONE}, * {@link #CALL_WAITING_SYNC_USER_CHANGE}, * {@link #CALL_WAITING_SYNC_FIRST_POWER_UP}, * {@link #CALL_WAITING_SYNC_FIRST_CHANGE}, * {@link #CALL_WAITING_SYNC_IMS_ONLY}. * * This configuration is valid only when * {@link #KEY_UT_TERMINAL_BASED_SERVICES_INT_ARRAY} includes * {@link #SUPPLEMENTARY_SERVICE_CW}. * *

If key is invalid or not configured, the default value * {@link #CALL_WAITING_SYNC_FIRST_CHANGE} will apply.

variables.name: KEY_TERMINAL_BASED_CALL_WAITING_DEFAULT_ENABLED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether the user setting for terminal-based call waiting
         * is enabled by default or not.
         * This configuration is valid only when
         * {@link #KEY_UT_TERMINAL_BASED_SERVICES_INT_ARRAY} includes
         * {@link #SUPPLEMENTARY_SERVICE_CW}.
         *
         * The default value for this key is {@code true}.
